\pard\intbl\ql
{{\b
Aims of the course: }}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{The aim of the course is to combine theoretical knowledge of macroeconomics 
and economic policy with practical applications in the field of financial 
market analysis\'2e The course focuses on the understanding of the 
national economy as an economic system, the interrelationships between 
the various macroeconomic aggregates, the nature of the creation and 
use of macroeconomic forecasts and their implications for the various 
segments of financial markets\'2e Attention will be paid to the links 
between the situation in financial markets and the emergence, course 
and consequences of financial and economic crises\'2e Recently, the 
role and importance of fiscal policy has been increasing, not only 
in the context of the ageing population and the associated rising 
government expenditure, but also in the context of the implementation 
of a stabilisation function within the framework of "post\_crisis" 
stimulation of aggregate demand\'2e Among other things, these factors 
are leading to an increase in government debt and hence to an increase 
in the issuance of government securities\'2e The course therefore 
also examines the repercussions of increased fiscal policy activity 
on financial markets\'2e}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{\~}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{{\b
Learning outcomes and competences: }}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{Upon successful completion, students will be able to:\line
\_ Understand the interlinkages between macroeconomic developments, 
economic policy actions and financial market developments, including 
their most significant manifestations and anomalies\'2e\line
\_ Be able to correctly use and interpret macroeconomic data in analyses\'2e 
\line
\_ To be familiar with basic macroeconomic aggregates, their interdependence 
on real data of the Czech economy\'2e Identify sources of possible 
macroeconomic imbalances\'2e\line
\_ \'46ind, understand and apply publicly available macroeconomic 
forecasts (CNB, Ministry of \'46inance, commercial banks) from the 
perspective of an economic policy maker, banker, corporation, household 
and financial market trader\'2e\line
\_ Understand and discuss the interrelationships between the various 
segments of financial markets and crisis phenomena of a financial 
and economic nature\'2e \line
\_ Understand the effects of fiscal policy and the structure of their 
revenues and expenditures on financial markets\'2e\line
\_ Define the specifics of government\_issued securities and their 
manifestations in financial markets\'2e\line
\_ Discuss the implications of the growing debt burden of the government 
sector on domestic and international financial markets\'2e}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{\~}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
