{1\'2e Interrelationships between macroeconomic and financial market 
developments\line
2\'2e\tab Macroeconomic data and macroeconomic analysis (content, 
structure and interpretation)\line
3\'2e\tab Use of basic macroeconomic identities in macroeconomic analyses\line
4\'2e\tab Macroeconomic forecasting and its reflection on financial 
markets\line
5\'2e\tab Macroeconomic sources of anomalies and irrationality in 
financial markets\line
6\'2e\tab The interrelationship between financial and economic crises\line
7\'2e The response of financial markets to government policy over 
the business cycle \line
8\'2e\tab The ageing population: a comparison of pension systems and 
their impact on financial markets\line
9\'2e\tab The impact of tax policy on the real economy and financial 
markets \line
10 Public debt financiers: reasons for holding government securities 
from the perspective of individual entities\line
11\'2e\tab Capacity and requirements of financial markets to become 
a creditor of the government sector\line
12\'2e Impacts and reflections of government debt on international 
financial markets}\cell\row\pard
